
                                            The fires broke out earlier this week. 
                                         CAPE TOWN - Fire crews have yet to extinguish two fires still raging in Gordon's Bay and the Red Hill area in Cape Town. The fires broke out earlier this week.  In Gordon's Bay, five homes were either damaged or destroyed.  The fires have been contained for now.  Cape Town Fire and Rescue Service's Theo Lane says they’re still monitoring the fires. “We still have two fire engines at Red Hill and two water tankers, assisted by Table Mountain National Parks.” WATCH: Cape ablaze: 2 fires ravage WC simultaneously  (Edited by Shimoney Regter)